snippet: Geno Smith scrambled away from traffic, drew a flag and gave the Jets a chance to win against the Buccaneers. He also gave Jets fans an unfamiliar feeling: confidence in the quarterback.
abstract: Greg Bishop On Pro Football column holds that New York Jets rookie quarterback Geno Smith gave Jets fans some reason to have confidence in their quarterback as he gave his team a chance to beat Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
lead_paragraph: Geno Smith scrambled away from traffic, drew a flag and gave the Jets a chance to win against the Buccaneers. He also gave Jets fans an unfamiliar feeling: confidence in the quarterback.

headline.main: Rookie May Not Be Perfect, but He Provides Reason to Hope
